        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-04-98 10:29 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">there were 100 gold c3po's given as door prizes at the 1997 International ToyExpo in philly last year ...i have 7</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Zapper</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-09-98 07:58 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Kewl! Do you know if that means their were<br>
            100 chrome finish Darth Vaders too? These<br>
            must be worth plenty if they are limited to only 100 of each? Any guess on a s&g pair's value?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>anthony</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-09-98 11:43 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">personally i wouldn't pay more than maybe $5 each for those puppies. there is just no way to prove they are from the show and they were not authorized. i could get some chrome or gold dip and coat 3 Hulks with it, would that make you pay obscene amount for one of them? but some people seem to be paying in excess of $100 for these SW items. heck, people are paying $10 for currents so why not?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezpimp</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-09-98 02:08 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">there is no value to these dispensors, you won't ever find them listed on a price guide (well, there not on any yet). these are fantasy dispensors and are worth waht someone wants to pay for them. i also wouldn't pay more than $5-$10 for one but some people might pay a lot. you never know.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Zapper</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-09-98 02:38 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I know what you mean. They may not be officialy licensed by LFL, I dont know. There<br>
            has to be some way to prove they came from<br>
            the ToyFair Expo? I mean these do not appear to be dipped in some coating, they look like they are made whole using the silver chrome for the base and the DV head may be coated with silver because it is heavy.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezpimp</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-10-98 09:06 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">ive never seen a pic of these (can someone send me one?) but there are people who do this. i have a silver dispensor (mickey) done by Hippy Pez (Gene Young) can someone go to my site to look at the pic under Glamour PEz and tell me if these toy expo dispensors are done similar, although the ones i have have little beads and stuff, they are really cool.</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">my site: http://www.globalserve.net/~pezcondo/</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">dispensor:<br>
            http://www.globalserve.net/~pezcondo/glam.jpg</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">thanks</font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-11-98 01:19 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">i have no clue how many chrome vaders were made, and i'm not positive that the c3pos were ONLY made for the toyexpo... all i can tell you is that (1.) they gave away 100 gold c3pos to the first 100 people through the door, (2.) the dispensers arrived in a big brown box with the pez logo stamped on the sides in navy blue, (3.) the copyright info on the back of the head is actually clearer to read than on the regular c3po, (4.) The dispensers are heavy, you'd have to feel them to understand, (5.) the little plastic tab on the inside that the candy sits on is actually more of a solid white color, not that frosty translucent color that the normal one is, (6.) the inside on the head and stem is all gold, but none of the mechanisms are... ..those are the only points i can think of to make ...any more questions?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Zapper</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-11-98 09:49 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I will try to get a photo of them both and put it up on my site. The LFL trademark on the C3PO is on the back of the head and is clearer than the mass produced one. It is heavier for sure, The pez body has a number<br>
            5 on the top right hand corner of one side, the DV has a number 1 in the same location.<br>
            The mass ones dont have this it seems. I got them from the eBay auction site and paid $65 for both of them, but I am a DieHard SW fan and I think they will be worth plenty more in the future. Because most of the Promotional pez given out at expos and trade shows are being sold for around $30-$35 and they are of the same limited quantity as these are. Alex, do you have just a C3PO? or do you have the DV one too?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-12-98 12:39 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">just c3po's ..i've never even seen the chrome vader... just heard about it</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Zapper</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-23-98 12:56 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I just got a email from the people that put on the Expo and this is what they said.</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">"We gave away 500 of each at The International collectable toy eXpo in<br>
            Philadelphia. this year's showw is this weekend at the South Jersey Expo<br>
            Center in Pennsauken. call (407) 331-SHOW (7469) for info."</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I asked Mike some more on where and how many were made, so I will post that info when I get it. Still waiting to scan them in :|<br></font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-25-98 09:31 PM CT (US)</font></font>
